<p><strong>Pie 9.0:</strong></p>

<p>After checkin with some other developers.  The Oreo version <em>should</em> be compatible with Android 9.0 Pie.  There are a couple things Iâ€™m tyring to work in to ensure that this is the case such as:  setting SELinux as permissive (<a href="https://github.com/AdrianDC/kernel_permissive_patcher/blob/master/kernel_permissive_patcher/kernel_permissive.sh">see potential patch by AdrianDC</a>), double checking that safety net is off and dm-verity is off.</p>

